            <title><![CDATA[The Best Marvel Rivals Tips, Steam Winter Sale Deals, And More Of The Week's Most Helpful Gaming Info]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-tips-steam-winter-sale-deals-1851726474</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/the-best-marvel-rivals-tips-steam-winter-sale-deals-and-more-of-the-weeks-most-helpful-gaming-info.1067445/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-tips-steam-winter-sale-deals-1851726474<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="a1d76914c87c3b1f03925231ef514136" data-recommend-id="image://a1d76914c87c3b1f03925231ef514136" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel Games / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Marvel Games / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Marvel / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Naughty Dog / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Team Jade / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Marvel Games<!-- -->, <!-- -->Poncle Limited<!-- -->, <!-- -->Valve / Activision / Ubisoft / Konami / Sony / Mossmouth / Big Mode / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Blizzard / Marvel Games / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Grinding Gear Games</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="a1d76914c87c3b1f03925231ef514136" data-recommend-id="image://a1d76914c87c3b1f03925231ef514136" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>This week, <em>Marvel Rivals </em>continued to pull players in with its enjoyably chaotic take on the hero-shooter genre, and we’ve got heaps of tips to help you come to grips with the game and see what cool strats other players are using. We’ll also fill you in on everything we know about <em>Intergalactic</em>, Naughty Dog’s upcoming game that got a captivating reveal at the Game Awards, and point you to some of the best deals in Steam’s Winter Sale, which is going on now.&nbsp;</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="2c7222e286fe4f7d71a1256e5b1aed06" data-recommend-id="image://2c7222e286fe4f7d71a1256e5b1aed06" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Spider-Man shoots his web towards the screen in his Scarlet Spider costume." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Spider-Man shoots his web towards the screen in his Scarlet Spider costume." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel Games / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="2c7222e286fe4f7d71a1256e5b1aed06" data-recommend-id="image://2c7222e286fe4f7d71a1256e5b1aed06" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Spider-Man shoots his web towards the screen in his Scarlet Spider costume." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Marvel Rivals </em>is quite a generous game. Not only are all future heroes confirmed to be free, but every battle pass can be enjoyed permanently as long as you’ve purchased them. You’ll mostly be tempted to put your money toward skins, but there are many you can acquire for free. - Samuel Moreno <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-hero-shooter-free-skins-ps5-psplus-1851721614&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-hero-shooter-free-skins-ps5-psplus-1851721614">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="57593d76ad563dc8741976e2715d7c72" data-recommend-id="image://57593d76ad563dc8741976e2715d7c72" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Psylocke poses with the moon as a backdrop in her Vengeance skin, based on her classic attire." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Psylocke poses with the moon as a backdrop in her Vengeance skin, based on her classic attire." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel Games / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="57593d76ad563dc8741976e2715d7c72" data-recommend-id="image://57593d76ad563dc8741976e2715d7c72" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Psylocke poses with the moon as a backdrop in her Vengeance skin, based on her classic attire." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Marvel Rivals</em> is the latest game to make a splash in the hero shooter scene, and it’s easy to see where it takes its inspiration from. That’s not to say the developers didn’t put enough of a unique spin on things. <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-hero-shooter-overwatch-team-attacks-how-1851718182&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-hero-shooter-overwatch-team-attacks-how-1851718182">Team-up abilities</a></span>, for example, are a special mechanic and there are quite a few other distinct terms to learn. A standout example of the latter is Ace, which depending on who you ask, might give you different definitions. - Samuel Moreno <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-ace-scoreboard-team-kill-mean-1851722529&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-ace-scoreboard-team-kill-mean-1851722529">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="f4ee1ae43b2f693ec6270e5c262a7f44" data-recommend-id="image://f4ee1ae43b2f693ec6270e5c262a7f44" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Jordan sips from a drink through a straw." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Jordan sips from a drink through a straw." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Naughty Dog / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="f4ee1ae43b2f693ec6270e5c262a7f44" data-recommend-id="image://f4ee1ae43b2f693ec6270e5c262a7f44" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Jordan sips from a drink through a straw." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Naughty Dog, the developer behind <em>The Last of Us</em>, <em>Uncharted</em>, <em>Jak &amp; Daxter</em>, and the original <em>Crash Bandicoot</em> games, finally revealed what it’s been working on since <em>The Last of Us Part II</em> launched in 2020. The game is called <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/intergalactic-heretic-prophet-last-of-us-naughty-dog-1851721022&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/intergalactic-heretic-prophet-last-of-us-naughty-dog-1851721022"><em>Intergalactic: The Heretic Prophet</em></a></span> and it’s coming to a PlayStation 5 near you. We saw the <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/naughty-dog-last-of-us-intergalatic-trailer-game-awards-1851720381&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/naughty-dog-last-of-us-intergalatic-trailer-game-awards-1851720381">first trailer for it at The Game Awards</a></span>, and in the days since, some more details have trickled out through interviews, blog posts, and social media. Read on for a recap of everything we’ve gleaned thus far about Naughty Dog’s next game. - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/intergalactic-heretic-prophet-naughty-dog-ps5-actors-1851722128&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/intergalactic-heretic-prophet-naughty-dog-ps5-actors-1851722128">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="36e499cc37f0a405000f575bdf987f6c" data-recommend-id="image://36e499cc37f0a405000f575bdf987f6c" data-format="png" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Magic beams surround Doctor Strange as he floats in the air." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Magic beams surround Doctor Strange as he floats in the air." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="36e499cc37f0a405000f575bdf987f6c" data-recommend-id="image://36e499cc37f0a405000f575bdf987f6c" data-format="png" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Magic beams surround Doctor Strange as he floats in the air." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Doctor Strange’s portal—a skill that lets the sorcerer create a pathway between any two points on the map—is one of the most useful abilities in <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-review-hero-shooter-overwatch-netease-1851717975&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-review-hero-shooter-overwatch-netease-1851717975"><em>Marvel Rivals</em></a></span>. Players have used it to set up game-changing plays like giving teammates a shortcut into the enemy backline, or sending foes falling to their deaths by putting a portal in front of their spawn point. Developer NetEase had already reduced the power of the portal <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-patch-notes-doctor-strange-portal-ult-1851717418&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-patch-notes-doctor-strange-portal-ult-1851717418">through the game’s first patch</a></span>, but given all the creative ways players are using it, I would not be surprised if we see this ability tweaked more in the coming months. Because now a streamer has probably found the most hilariously broken way to use it I’ve seen thus far. - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-doctor-strange-portal-combo-exploit-kills-1851723986&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-doctor-strange-portal-combo-exploit-kills-1851723986">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="a2fd4738c14b054714f42f537daae0d8" data-recommend-id="image://a2fd4738c14b054714f42f537daae0d8" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot witha battle tank and helicopter for Delta Force features Steam user reviews." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot witha battle tank and helicopter for Delta Force features Steam user reviews." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Team Jade / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="a2fd4738c14b054714f42f537daae0d8" data-recommend-id="image://a2fd4738c14b054714f42f537daae0d8" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot witha battle tank and helicopter for Delta Force features Steam user reviews." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>It seems like every year or two, we have a new “<em>Battlefield</em>-killer” storming the market in the hopes of gaining a following within the large-scale first-person shooter market. Following the absolute disaster of <em>Battlefield 2042</em>, there’s a pretty large hole to fill. But is <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://store.steampowered.com/app/2507950/Delta_Force/&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/2507950/Delta_Force/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Delta Force</em></a></span>—the free-to-play first-person shooter from developer Team Jade—destined to take the long-running franchise’s place? Probably not. But it’s still a competent, easy-to-dive-into multiplayer shooter with plenty going for it on launch. - Brandon Morgan <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/delta-force-battlefield-cod-reviews-good-free-to-play-1851723082&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/delta-force-battlefield-cod-reviews-good-free-to-play-1851723082">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="42e68b8785cc0f40378ba35aa1d4af4e" data-recommend-id="image://42e68b8785cc0f40378ba35aa1d4af4e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Venom emits tendrils from his body to attack Namor, Spider-Man, and The Punisher all at the same time." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Venom emits tendrils from his body to attack Namor, Spider-Man, and The Punisher all at the same time." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel Games</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="42e68b8785cc0f40378ba35aa1d4af4e" data-recommend-id="image://42e68b8785cc0f40378ba35aa1d4af4e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Venom emits tendrils from his body to attack Namor, Spider-Man, and The Punisher all at the same time." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Marvel Rivals</em> might not feature a post-match ”Play of the Game” like <em>Overwatch</em>, but every match highlights the most valuable player, or MVP at the end. You can also see the MVP highlighted on the match summary screen if you were on their team. If you weren’t, you would instead see another player with an SVP title. - Samuel Moreno <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-svp-mean-rank-competitive-play-1851722265&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-svp-mean-rank-competitive-play-1851722265">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="64a376d441cfb7512c68171c67ff3217" data-recommend-id="image://64a376d441cfb7512c68171c67ff3217" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image shows some game covers in front of the Steam winter sale logo. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An image shows some game covers in front of the Steam winter sale logo. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Valve / Activision / Ubisoft / Konami / Sony / Mossmouth / Big Mode / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="64a376d441cfb7512c68171c67ff3217" data-recommend-id="image://64a376d441cfb7512c68171c67ff3217" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image shows some game covers in front of the Steam winter sale logo. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>The Steam Winter Sale is now live, bringing with it some big deals on new and old games including <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/animal-well-review-metroidvania-puzzle-2024-goty-1851465730&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/animal-well-review-metroidvania-puzzle-2024-goty-1851465730"><em>Animal Well</em></a></span><em>, Call of Duty, Star Wars Outlaws, </em><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dead-space-2023-remake-review-kotaku-pc-ps5-1850050062&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dead-space-2023-remake-review-kotaku-pc-ps5-1850050062"><em>Dead Space</em></a></span><em>, Mass Effect</em>, and many, <em>many </em>more.  - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/steam-winter-sale-christmas-best-deals-pc-biggest-valve-1851725607&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/steam-winter-sale-christmas-best-deals-pc-biggest-valve-1851725607">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="14a6db04005e117985c9b49b37720d8c" data-recommend-id="image://14a6db04005e117985c9b49b37720d8c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Baptiste and Rocket Raccoon are juxtaposed next to each other." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Baptiste and Rocket Raccoon are juxtaposed next to each other." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Blizzard / Marvel Games / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="14a6db04005e117985c9b49b37720d8c" data-recommend-id="image://14a6db04005e117985c9b49b37720d8c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Baptiste and Rocket Raccoon are juxtaposed next to each other." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Marvel Rivals </em>is the newest hero shooter on the block, following closely in <em>Overwatch</em>’s footsteps. It takes inspiration from Blizzard’s game in plenty of ways, from general game modes to its style of monetization. Another way it takes inspiration is in its characters. - Parker Johnson <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-overwatch-2-heroes-similar-main-1851725562&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-overwatch-2-heroes-similar-main-1851725562">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="d5d667d9ac6ece7e71337379bc250729" data-recommend-id="image://d5d667d9ac6ece7e71337379bc250729" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Official artwork for the Mercenary class in Path of Exile 2 shows a person in a cloak with a crossbow." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Official artwork for the Mercenary class in Path of Exile 2 shows a person in a cloak with a crossbow." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Grinding Gear Games</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="d5d667d9ac6ece7e71337379bc250729" data-recommend-id="image://d5d667d9ac6ece7e71337379bc250729" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Official artwork for the Mercenary class in Path of Exile 2 shows a person in a cloak with a crossbow." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>When starting an RPG, before you even consider a character creator (which<em> Path of Exile 2</em> does not offer), there’s a choice—the ultimate choice for a beginner. What is the best starting class for a new player? Is it the tried-and-tested Warrior? Perhaps the ever-vigilant Ranger? - Brandon Morgan <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/path-of-exile-2-mercenary-class-guide-beginners-best-1851721613&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/path-of-exile-2-mercenary-class-guide-beginners-best-1851721613">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
